I also note that following the release of your report was the announcement of the continuation of the Trans-Pacific Trade Agreement. Unfortunately, Labour and the Greens united to repeal the remaining parts of this Agreement that protect our agricultural exports and continue to drag our feet in the trade negotiations.

We need to protect our agricultural sector, our families and our exporters, who fund our essential public services. It is pleasing to see that New Zealand is moving into the future sustainably. Let’s have a government that moves forward with intent and vision.

Best wishes

Marama Fox

Co-leader, Māori Party

(Queue applause)

22. Gun Safety

METIRIA TUREI (Co-Leader—Green) : I move that the House call the 51st New Zealand Parliament into continuous session under urgency without delay to consider the only legislative priority this Parliament—new laws that will save lives by keeping guns out of the hands of gangs, criminals, and domestic abusers—

Mr SPEAKER: Order! The member has moved clause 2 of her original agreement, that the House immediately consider this Bill. The House is not in continuous committee. What the Labour leader wants to do is move his amendment once we are in continuous committee. Specific question:
